              </div>
              <div class="fz-panel" id="ma_utubep" style="display:none;">
                <h3>Manometer</h3>
                <div class="fz-ctl"><label>Gauge pressure p (kPa) <span id="ma_pgV">20</span></label><input id="ma_pg" type="range" min="-40" max="80" step="1" value="20"/></div>
                <div class="fz-ctl"><label>Manometer fluid SG <span id="ma_sgV">13.6</span></label><input id="ma_sg" type="range" min="0.8" max="13.6" step="0.1" value="13.6"/></div>
                <div class="fz-ctl"><label>Connected fluid SG <span id="ma_sgcV">1.0</span></label><input id="ma_sgc" type="range" min="0.001" max="2" step="0.001" value="1"/></div>
                <div class="fz-ctl"><label>Limb separation height a (m) <span id="ma_aV">0.30</span></label><input id="ma_a" type="range" min="0" max="1" step="0.02" value="0.3"/></div>
              </div>
              <div class="fz-panel">
                <h3>Results</h3>
                <div class="fz-metric"><span class="fz-metric-l">Gauge pressure</span><span class="fz-metric-v amber" id="ma_pgauge">&mdash;</span></div>
                <div class="fz-metric"><span class="fz-metric-l">Absolute pressure</span><span class="fz-metric-v" id="ma_pabs">&mdash;</span></div>
                <div class="fz-metric"><span class="fz-metric-l">Pressure head</span><span class="fz-metric-v green" id="ma_head">&mdash;</span></div>
                <div class="fz-metric"><span class="fz-metric-l">Manometer deflection</span><span class="fz-metric-v purple" id="ma_defl">&mdash;</span></div>
                <div class="fz-metric"><span class="fz-metric-l">Equivalent water column</span><span class="fz-metric-v" id="ma_weq">&mdash;</span></div>
              </div>
            </aside>
            <div>
              <div class="fz-panel">
                <h3>Apparatus</h3>
                <canvas id="ma_cv" class="fz-cv" width="760" height="440"></canvas>
                <div class="fz-note">In depth mode the gauge measures p = p0 + rho g h, rising linearly with depth. In U-tube mode the heavy manometer fluid is displaced by the applied pressure; the deflection reads the head difference.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="fz-panel">
                <h3>Pressure variation with depth</h3>
                <canvas id="ma_curve" class="fz-cv" width="760" height="200"></canvas>
                <div class="fz-formula"><b>p = p0 + rho g h</b> (hydrostatic)&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; U-tube: <b>p = (rho_m - rho_c) g h_def + rho_c g a</b>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; head = p / rho g.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="fz-sec" data-sec="aim"><div class="fz-prose"><p>To study the linear variation of hydrostatic pressure with depth in a static liquid, to express pressures as equivalent fluid heads, and to read a gauge pressure difference with a U-tube manometer using a heavier indicating fluid.</p></div></div>

        <div class="fz-sec" data-sec="theory"><div class="fz-prose">
          <p>In a fluid at rest the pressure increases linearly with depth because each layer must support the weight of the column above it. The hydrostatic law follows from a force balance on a fluid element. A manometer turns this law into a measuring instrument: the unknown pressure displaces a column of indicating fluid, and the deflection &mdash; multiplied by the difference in specific weights &mdash; gives the pressure.</p>
          <div class="eqs">
            Hydrostatic law:&nbsp; <b>p = p0 + rho g h</b><br/>
            Pressure head:&nbsp; <b>h_p = p / (rho g)</b><br/>
            U-tube (heavy fluid):&nbsp; <b>p = (rho_m - rho_c) g h_def + rho_c g a</b><br/>
            Equivalent water column:&nbsp; h_water = p / (rho_water g)
          </div>
          <p>Mercury (SG 13.6) gives a small, readable deflection for large pressures; lighter oils give a magnified deflection for small pressures.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="fz-sec" data-sec="proc"><div class="fz-prose"><ol>
          <li>In depth mode, choose the liquid and move the depth probe; read the gauge pressure.</li>
          <li>Confirm the pressure varies linearly with depth from the curve.</li>
          <li>Express the pressure as an equivalent head and an equivalent water column.</li>
          <li>Switch to U-tube mode and apply a gauge pressure.</li>
          <li>Watch the manometer columns displace and read the deflection.</li>
          <li>Change the manometer fluid SG and see the deflection scale inversely with its weight.</li>
        </ol></div></div>

        <div class="fz-sec" data-sec="quiz"><div class="fz-quiz" data-quiz="mano"></div></div>

        <div class="fz-sec" data-sec="ref"><div class="fz-prose"><ul class="refs">
          <li>F. M. White, Fluid Mechanics, 8th ed., McGraw-Hill, Ch. 2 (Pressure distribution).</li>
          <li>B. R. Munson et al., Fundamentals of Fluid Mechanics, Wiley, Ch. 2 (Fluid statics).</li>
          <li>IIT Virtual Labs &mdash; Fluid Mechanics: Manometry, vlabs.ac.in.</li>
        </ul></div></div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</main>

<script is:inline>
(function () {
  var G = 9.81;
  function el(id) { return document.getElementById(id); }
  function v(id) { return parseFloat(el(id).value); }
  function fmt(val, d) { if (!isFinite(val)) return '—'; return val.toFixed(d === undefined ? 2 : d); }
  function setTxt(id, s) { var n = el(id); if (n) n.textContent = s; }
  function clamp(x, lo, hi) { return x < lo ? lo : (x > hi ? hi : x); }

  /* ---------- fluid property tables ---------- */
  // density kg/m3, dynamic viscosity Pa.s, vapour pressure kPa (abs)
  var FLUIDS = {
    water:    { name: 'Water (20 C)',     rho: 998,  mu: 0.001002, pv: 2.34 },
    seawater: { name: 'Seawater',         rho: 1025, mu: 0.00107,  pv: 2.34 },
    oil:      { name: 'Light oil (SAE10)', rho: 870,  mu: 0.082,    pv: 0.5 },
    glycerin: { name: 'Glycerin',         rho: 1260, mu: 0.95,     pv: 0.01 },
    kerosene: { name: 'Kerosene',         rho: 800,  mu: 0.00164,  pv: 3.2 },
    air:      { name: 'Air (sea level)',  rho: 1.204, mu: 0.0000182, pv: 0 }
  };
  var FLUID_ORDER = ['water', 'seawater', 'oil', 'glycerin', 'kerosene', 'air'];
  function fillFluidSelect(sel, withAir) {
    for (var i = 0; i < FLUID_ORDER.length; i++) {
      var k = FLUID_ORDER[i];
      if (!withAir && k === 'air') continue;
      var o = document.createElement('option');
      o.value = k; o.textContent = FLUIDS[k].name;
      sel.appendChild(o);
    }
  }
  // water density / viscosity vs temperature (deg C) — fits valid 0..100 C
  function waterRho(T) { return 1000 * (1 - (T + 288.9414) / (508929.2 * (T + 68.12963)) * (T - 3.9863) * (T - 3.9863)); }
  function waterMu(T) {
    // Vogel-type fit (Pa.s)
    return 0.001 * Math.exp(-3.7188 + 578.919 / (T + 137.546 - 0)) / Math.exp(-3.7188 + 578.919 / 137.546) * 1.002;
  }

  /* ================================================================
     Experiment navigation + section tabs
     ================================================================ */
  var exps = el('expList').querySelectorAll('.fz-exp');
  var sections = document.querySelectorAll('.fz-experiment');
  for (var ei = 0; ei < exps.length; ei++) {
    (function (btn) {
      btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        var key = btn.getAttribute('data-exp');
        for (var j = 0; j < exps.length; j++) exps[j].classList.remove('active');
        btn.classList.add('active');
        for (var s = 0; s < sections.length; s++) {
          sections[s].classList.toggle('active', sections[s].getAttribute('data-exp') === key);
        }
      });
    })(exps[ei]);
  }
  for (var si = 0; si < sections.length; si++) {
    (function (sec) {
      var tabs = sec.querySelectorAll('.fz-tab');
      for (var t = 0; t < tabs.length; t++) {
        (function (tb) {
          tb.addEventListener('click', function () {
            var key = tb.getAttribute('data-sec');
            for (var k = 0; k < tabs.length; k++) tabs[k].classList.remove('active');
            tb.classList.add('active');
            var panes = sec.querySelectorAll('.fz-sec');
            for (var p = 0; p < panes.length; p++) {
              panes[p].classList.toggle('active', panes[p].getAttribute('data-sec') === key);
            }
          });
        })(tabs[t]);
      }
    })(sections[si]);
  }

  /* ================================================================
     Canvas helpers
     ================================================================ */
  function ctxOf(id) {
    var c = el(id);
    if (!c) return null;
    return { c: c, x: c.getContext('2d'), w: c.width, h: c.height };
  }
  function clearCv(g, bg) {
    g.x.fillStyle = bg || '#070a0d';
    g.x.fillRect(0, 0, g.w, g.h);
  }
  function line(x, a, b, cc, dd, col, lw) {
    x.beginPath(); x.moveTo(a, b); x.lineTo(cc, dd);
    x.strokeStyle = col; x.lineWidth = lw || 1; x.stroke();
  }
  function label(x, tx, px, py, col, sz, align) {
    x.fillStyle = col; x.font = (sz || 11) + 'px Geist Mono, ui-monospace, monospace';
    x.textAlign = align || 'left'; x.textBaseline = 'alphabetic';
    x.fillText(tx, px, py);
  }

  /* ================================================================
     Self-assessment engine
     ================================================================ */
  var QUIZZES = {
    bern: [
      { q: 'A pipe narrows so its area halves (A2 = A1/2). For steady incompressible flow the throat velocity is:',
        opts: ['Half v1', 'The same as v1', 'Twice v1', 'Four times v1'],
        a: 2, e: 'Continuity A1 v1 = A2 v2 gives v2 = (A1/A2) v1 = 2 v1.' },
      { q: 'Where the velocity is highest in a horizontal venturi, the static pressure is:',
        opts: ['Highest', 'Lowest', 'Unchanged', 'Atmospheric'],
        a: 1, e: 'Bernoulli: as velocity head rises the pressure head must fall — pressure is lowest at the throat.' },
      { q: 'Bernoulli\'s equation in head form states that the constant total head equals:',
        opts: ['p/rho g only', 'v^2/2g only', 'p/rho g + v^2/2g + z', 'rho g h'],
        a: 2, e: 'Total head = pressure head + velocity head + elevation head, constant along a streamline for ideal flow.' },
      { q: 'If the throat static pressure falls to the liquid\'s vapour pressure, the likely result is:',
        opts: ['Faster flow with no effect', 'Cavitation (vapour bubbles)', 'The flow stops', 'The density doubles'],
        a: 1, e: 'At the vapour pressure the liquid boils locally, forming cavitation bubbles that can damage the pipe.' }
    ],
    reyn: [
      { q: 'The Reynolds number Re = rho v D / mu represents the ratio of:',
        opts: ['Pressure to gravity forces', 'Inertial to viscous forces', 'Surface tension to inertia', 'Heat to work'],
        a: 1, e: 'Re is inertial forces divided by viscous forces; high Re means inertia dominates and flow turns turbulent.' },
      { q: 'In a circular pipe, flow is generally laminar when:',
        opts: ['Re > 4000', 'Re < 2300', 'Re = 10000', 'Re is negative'],
        a: 1, e: 'Below about Re = 2300 viscous damping keeps pipe flow orderly and laminar.' },
      { q: 'Warming the water (lower viscosity) at fixed velocity and diameter makes the Reynolds number:',
        opts: ['Smaller', 'Larger', 'Unchanged', 'Zero'],
        a: 1, e: 'Re is inversely proportional to mu; lower viscosity raises Re, pushing the flow toward turbulence.' },
      { q: 'The velocity profile of fully-developed laminar pipe flow is:',
        opts: ['Flat (uniform)', 'Parabolic', 'Linear', 'Triangular'],
        a: 1, e: 'Hagen-Poiseuille flow is parabolic; turbulent flow is flatter due to cross-stream mixing.' }
    ],
    fric: [
      { q: 'The Darcy-Weisbach head loss hf = f (L/D)(v^2/2g) varies with pipe length L as:',
        opts: ['Inversely with L', 'Linearly with L', 'With L^2', 'Independent of L'],
        a: 1, e: 'Head loss is directly proportional to length L for a given diameter and velocity.' },
      { q: 'For laminar pipe flow the Darcy friction factor is:',
        opts: ['64 / Re', 'Re / 64', '0.316 Re^-0.25', 'Independent of Re'],
        a: 0, e: 'In laminar flow f = 64/Re exactly, independent of wall roughness.' },
      { q: 'In fully-rough turbulent flow, the friction factor depends mainly on:',
        opts: ['Reynolds number only', 'Relative roughness e/D', 'Fluid density only', 'Pipe length'],
        a: 1, e: 'At high Re the Colebrook curve flattens; f becomes a function of e/D alone.' },
      { q: 'Doubling the flow rate in a turbulent pipe (f roughly constant) changes the head loss by about:',
        opts: ['x2', 'x4', 'x0.5', 'No change'],
        a: 1, e: 'hf scales with v^2, so doubling the flow roughly quadruples the friction head loss.' }
    ],
    vent: [
      { q: 'The discharge through a venturi meter is proportional to:',
        opts: ['The pressure difference dp', 'The square root of dp', 'dp squared', 'The reciprocal of dp'],
        a: 1, e: 'Q = Cd A2 sqrt(2 dp / (rho(1-beta^4))), so Q is proportional to the square root of the head.' },
      { q: 'Compared with a venturi, a sharp-edged orifice plate typically has a discharge coefficient that is:',
        opts: ['Higher (about 0.98)', 'Lower (about 0.6)', 'Greater than 1', 'Exactly 1'],
        a: 1, e: 'The orifice contracts strongly at the vena contracta, giving Cd near 0.6; the venturi recovers more, Cd near 0.98.' },
      { q: 'The discharge coefficient Cd corrects the meter equation for:',
        opts: ['Compressibility only', 'Real energy losses and jet contraction', 'Temperature', 'Gravity'],
        a: 1, e: 'Cd accounts for friction losses and the contraction of the real jet relative to the ideal Bernoulli flow.' },
      { q: 'A mercury manometer (SG 13.6) reading a deflection h over water gives a pressure difference of:',
        opts: ['rho_w g h', '(13.6 - 1) rho_w g h', '13.6 rho_w g h', 'h only'],
        a: 1, e: 'dp = (SG_m - 1) rho_water g h, the difference of specific weights times the deflection.' }
    ],
    torr: [
      { q: 'Torricelli\'s theorem gives the ideal efflux velocity from an orifice under head h as:',
        opts: ['g h', 'sqrt(2 g h)', '2 g h', 'sqrt(g h)'],
        a: 1, e: 'Bernoulli between the free surface and the jet gives v = sqrt(2 g h).' },
      { q: 'As a tank drains through a fixed orifice, the jet velocity:',
        opts: ['Stays constant', 'Increases', 'Decreases as the head falls', 'Reverses'],
        a: 2, e: 'v = sqrt(2 g h) falls as the head h drops, so the jet slows and its range shortens.' },
      { q: 'The time to empty a constant-area tank through an orifice is proportional to:',
        opts: ['H0', 'sqrt(H0)', 'H0 squared', '1/H0'],
        a: 1, e: 'Integrating the unsteady drain gives t_empty proportional to sqrt(H0) for a prismatic tank.' },
      { q: 'The coefficient of discharge Cd of a sharp-edged orifice is roughly:',
        opts: ['0.62', '1.0', '1.5', '0.10'],
        a: 0, e: 'Cd is about 0.62 (the product of contraction ~0.64 and velocity ~0.97 coefficients).' }
    ],
    mano: [
      { q: 'In a static liquid the gauge pressure at depth h below the free surface is:',
        opts: ['rho g h', 'rho g / h', 'h / rho g', 'rho / (g h)'],
        a: 0, e: 'The hydrostatic law gives gauge pressure p = rho g h, increasing linearly with depth.' },
      { q: 'A pressure of 1 atm (101 kPa) corresponds to a column of water about:',
        opts: ['1.0 m', '10.3 m', '101 m', '0.76 m'],
        a: 1, e: 'h = p/(rho g) = 101000/(998*9.81) ~ 10.3 m of water (or 0.76 m of mercury).' },
      { q: 'For the same pressure, a manometer fluid that is heavier gives a deflection that is:',
        opts: ['Larger', 'Smaller', 'Unchanged', 'Zero'],
        a: 1, e: 'Deflection = p / ((rho_m - rho_c) g); a heavier indicating fluid gives a smaller, more compact reading.' },
      { q: 'Hydrostatic pressure at a point in a connected static fluid depends on:',
        opts: ['The container shape', 'Only the vertical depth and fluid density', 'The total volume', 'The surface area'],
        a: 1, e: 'Pressure depends only on depth and density (Pascal/hydrostatic paradox), not on the vessel shape.' }
    ]
  };

  function buildQuiz(host) {
    var key = host.getAttribute('data-quiz');
    var items = QUIZZES[key];
    if (!items) return;
    var name = 'fq_' + key + '_';
    for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
      (function (it, idx) {
        var card = document.createElement('div');
        card.className = 'fz-q';
        var head = document.createElement('div');
        head.className = 'qhead';
        head.innerHTML = '<span class="qn">Q' + (idx + 1) + '</span>';
        head.appendChild(document.createTextNode(it.q));
        card.appendChild(head);
        for (var o = 0; o < it.opts.length; o++) {
          (function (oi) {
            var lab = document.createElement('label');
            lab.className = 'fz-opt';
            var inp = document.createElement('input');
            inp.type = 'radio'; inp.name = name + idx; inp.value = oi;
            lab.appendChild(inp);
            lab.appendChild(document.createTextNode(it.opts[oi]));
            card.appendChild(lab);
          })(o);
        }
        var expl = document.createElement('div');
        expl.className = 'fz-expl';
        card.appendChild(expl);
        host.appendChild(card);
      })(items[i], i);
    }
    var bar = document.createElement('div');
    var btn = document.createElement('button');
    btn.className = 'fz-check'; btn.textContent = 'Check answers';
    var score = document.createElement('span');
    score.className = 'fz-score';
    bar.appendChild(btn); bar.appendChild(score);
    host.appendChild(bar);
    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var cards = host.querySelectorAll('.fz-q');
      var correct = 0;
      for (var c = 0; c < cards.length; c++) {
        var it = items[c];
        var opts = cards[c].querySelectorAll('.fz-opt');
        var chosen = -1;
        for (var o = 0; o < opts.length; o++) {
          opts[o].classList.remove('correct', 'wrong');
          var radio = opts[o].querySelector('input');
          if (radio.checked) chosen = o;
        }
        opts[it.a].classList.add('correct');
        if (chosen === it.a) correct++;
        else if (chosen >= 0) opts[chosen].classList.add('wrong');
        var expl = cards[c].querySelector('.fz-expl');
        expl.className = 'fz-expl show ' + (chosen === it.a ? 'ok' : 'no');
        expl.textContent = (chosen === it.a ? 'Correct. ' : 'Not quite. ') + it.e;
      }
      score.textContent = correct + ' / ' + items.length + ' correct';
    });
  }
  var quizHosts = document.querySelectorAll('.fz-quiz');
  for (var qh = 0; qh < quizHosts.length; qh++) buildQuiz(quizHosts[qh]);

  /* a single shared animation phase for advecting particles */
  var phase = 0;
  var anims = [];
  function loop() {
    phase += 0.016;
    for (var i = 0; i < anims.length; i++) anims[i]();
    requestAnimationFrame(loop);
  }

  /* ================================================================
     EXPERIMENT 1 — BERNOULLI + CONTINUITY
     ================================================================ */
  (function () {
    var fluidSel = el('be_fluid');
    fillFluidSelect(fluidSel, false);
    fluidSel.value = 'water';

    // pipe profile: x in 0..1, radius factor; converging-diverging
    var N = 120;
    // station radii built each solve from D1 -> D2 -> back toward D1*0.85
    var beParticles = [];
    function initParticles() {
      beParticles = [];
      for (var i = 0; i < 90; i++) {
        beParticles.push({ s: Math.random(), lane: Math.random() * 2 - 1 });
      }
    }
    initParticles();

    function radiusAt(s, r1, r2) {
      // s in 0..1. Throat at s=0.5. Smooth cosine converging-diverging.
      // inlet radius r1, throat r2, outlet returns toward r1.
      var t;
      if (s < 0.5) {
        t = s / 0.5; // 0..1
        return r1 + (r2 - r1) * (0.5 - 0.5 * Math.cos(Math.PI * t));
      } else {
        t = (s - 0.5) / 0.5;
        return r2 + (r1 - r2) * (0.5 - 0.5 * Math.cos(Math.PI * t));
      }
    }

    function solve() {
      var f = FLUIDS[fluidSel.value];
      var rho = f.rho;
      var D1 = v('be_D1') / 100, D2 = v('be_D2') / 100; // m
      var Q = v('be_Q') / 1000; // m3/s
      var z2 = v('be_z');
      var p1 = v('be_p') * 1000; // Pa gauge
      var A1 = Math.PI * D1 * D1 / 4;
      var A2 = Math.PI * D2 * D2 / 4;
      var v1 = Q / A1, v2 = Q / A2;
      // Bernoulli between inlet (z=0) and throat (z=z2)
      var p2 = p1 + 0.5 * rho * (v1 * v1 - v2 * v2) - rho * G * z2;
      var dp = p1 - p2;
      var H = p1 / (rho * G) + v1 * v1 / (2 * G) + 0;
      setTxt('be_D1V', fmt(v('be_D1'), 1));
      setTxt('be_D2V', fmt(v('be_D2'), 1));
      setTxt('be_QV', fmt(v('be_Q'), 1));
      setTxt('be_zV', fmt(z2, 2));
      setTxt('be_pV', fmt(v('be_p'), 0));
      setTxt('be_A1', fmt(A1 * 1e4, 1) + ' cm2');
      setTxt('be_A2', fmt(A2 * 1e4, 1) + ' cm2');
      setTxt('be_v1', fmt(v1, 2) + ' m/s');
      setTxt('be_v2', fmt(v2, 2) + ' m/s');
      setTxt('be_ar', fmt(A1 / A2, 2) + ' : 1');
      setTxt('be_p2', fmt(p2 / 1000, 1) + ' kPa');
      setTxt('be_dp', fmt(dp / 1000, 1) + ' kPa');
      setTxt('be_H', fmt(H, 2) + ' m');
      // cavitation: absolute throat pressure vs vapour pressure
      var p2abs = p2 + 101325;
      var cavEl = el('be_cav');
      if (p2abs <= f.pv * 1000 + 5000) { cavEl.textContent = 'HIGH'; cavEl.className = 'fz-metric-v red'; }
      else if (p2abs <= f.pv * 1000 + 30000) { cavEl.textContent = 'moderate'; cavEl.className = 'fz-metric-v amber'; }
      else { cavEl.textContent = 'low'; cavEl.className = 'fz-metric-v green'; }

      return { rho: rho, D1: D1, D2: D2, Q: Q, A1: A1, A2: A2, v1: v1, v2: v2, p1: p1, p2: p2, z2: z2, H: H, f: f };
    }

    var st = null;
    function recompute() { st = solve(); drawHead(); drawEgl(); }

    var ids = ['be_D1', 'be_D2', 'be_Q', 'be_z', 'be_p'];
    for (var i = 0; i < ids.length; i++) el(ids[i]).addEventListener('input', recompute);
    fluidSel.addEventListener('change', recompute);

    function pipeY(g, s, sign) {
      var midY = g.h * 0.42;
      var r1 = g.h * 0.20, r2px = r1 * (st.D2 / st.D1);
      var r = radiusAt(s, r1, r2px);
      return midY - sign * r;
    }
    function pipeRadiusPx(g, s) {
      var r1 = g.h * 0.20, r2px = r1 * (st.D2 / st.D1);
      return radiusAt(s, r1, r2px);
    }
    function localVel(s) {
      // continuity: v ~ 1/area ~ 1/r^2
      var r1 = st.D1 / 2, r2 = st.D2 / 2;
      var r = radiusAt(s, r1, r2);
      var A = Math.PI * r * r;
      return st.Q / A;
    }
    function localP(s) {
      // Bernoulli along pipe, elevation interpolates 0->z2->0
      var vl = localVel(s);
      var zl = (s < 0.5) ? st.z2 * (s / 0.5) : st.z2 * (1 - (s - 0.5) / 0.5);
      // approximate elevation profile peaking at throat
      return st.p1 + 0.5 * st.rho * (st.v1 * st.v1 - vl * vl) - st.rho * G * zl;
    }

    function drawApparatus() {
      var g = ctxOf('be_cv'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var left = 40, right = g.w - 30, span = right - left;
      var midY = g.h * 0.42;
      // pipe outline (top & bottom)
      g.x.beginPath();
      var s, px, py;
      for (s = 0; s <= 1.0001; s += 1 / N) {
        px = left + s * span; py = pipeY(g, s, 1);
        if (s === 0) g.x.moveTo(px, py); else g.x.lineTo(px, py);
      }
      for (s = 1; s >= -0.0001; s -= 1 / N) {
        px = left + s * span; py = pipeY(g, s, -1);
        g.x.lineTo(px, py);
      }
      g.x.closePath();
      g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.07)';
      g.x.fill();
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#2b5a6e'; g.x.lineWidth = 2; g.x.stroke();

      // pressure-coloured fill bands by velocity
      var maxV = Math.max(st.v2, st.v1);
      for (s = 0; s < 1; s += 0.02) {
        var vl = localVel(s);
        var t = clamp(vl / (maxV * 1.05), 0, 1);
        var col = 'rgba(' + Math.round(56 + t * 190) + ',' + Math.round(189 - t * 100) + ',' + Math.round(248 - t * 180) + ',0.10)';
        var x0 = left + s * span, x1 = left + (s + 0.02) * span;
        var rTop = midY - pipeRadiusPx(g, s), rBot = midY + pipeRadiusPx(g, s);
        g.x.fillStyle = col;
        g.x.fillRect(x0, rTop, x1 - x0 + 1, rBot - rTop);
      }

      // particles advect at local velocity
      var dt = 0.016;
      for (var i = 0; i < beParticles.length; i++) {
        var p = beParticles[i];
        var vl = localVel(p.s);
        p.s += (vl / (st.v1 * 4 + 0.001)) * dt * 0.9;
        if (p.s > 1) { p.s -= 1; p.lane = Math.random() * 2 - 1; }
        var rpx = pipeRadiusPx(g, p.s) * 0.82;
        px = left + p.s * span;
        py = midY + p.lane * rpx;
        var spd = vl / maxV;
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(' + Math.round(120 + spd * 130) + ',230,255,0.9)';
        g.x.beginPath(); g.x.arc(px, py, 2.1, 0, 6.283); g.x.fill();
        // streak
        line(g.x, px, py, px - clamp(vl * 3, 4, 16), py, 'rgba(125,211,252,0.35)', 1);
      }

      // piezometer tubes at 3 stations
      var stations = [0.08, 0.5, 0.92];
      var names = ['1', 'throat', '2'];
      var pmaxhead = st.p1 / (st.rho * G) + 0.5;
      for (var k = 0; k < stations.length; k++) {
        var ss = stations[k];
        var pl = localP(ss);
        var head = pl / (st.rho * G);
        var sx = left + ss * span;
        var topPipe = midY - pipeRadiusPx(g, ss);
        // tube rises above pipe; height scaled
        var tubeBase = topPipe;
        var maxTubeH = g.h * 0.32;
        var colH = clamp(head / pmaxhead, 0.03, 1) * maxTubeH;
        // glass tube
        g.x.strokeStyle = '#3a4a55'; g.x.lineWidth = 1.5;
        g.x.strokeRect(sx - 5, tubeBase - maxTubeH, 10, maxTubeH);
        // water column
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.55)';
        g.x.fillRect(sx - 4, tubeBase - colH, 8, colH);
        label(g.x, fmt(head, 2) + 'm', sx, tubeBase - maxTubeH - 6, '#7dd3fc', 10, 'center');
        label(g.x, names[k], sx, midY + pipeRadiusPx(g, ss) + 16, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'center');
      }

      // flow arrow + labels
      label(g.x, 'flow', left + 6, midY - pipeRadiusPx(g, 0.05) - 6, '#5eead4', 11, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'D1 ' + fmt(v('be_D1'), 1) + 'cm', left + 6, g.h - 12, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'D2 ' + fmt(v('be_D2'), 1) + 'cm', left + span * 0.5, g.h - 12, '#fbbf24', 10, 'center');
    }

    function drawHead() {
      var g = ctxOf('be_head'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var L = 38, R = g.w - 14, B = g.h - 26, T = 14;
      // three head components stacked as bars at 3 stations
      var stns = [0.08, 0.5, 0.92];
      var labels = ['Sec 1', 'Throat', 'Sec 2'];
      var maxH = st.H * 1.1 + 0.5;
      var bw = (R - L) / 3 - 16;
      for (var k = 0; k < 3; k++) {
        var ss = stns[k];
        var vl = localVel(ss);
        var pl = localP(ss);
        var hp = pl / (st.rho * G);
        var hv = vl * vl / (2 * G);
        var x0 = L + k * ((R - L) / 3) + 8;
        function yOf(val) { return B - (val / maxH) * (B - T); }
        // pressure head (blue)
        var yp = yOf(hp);
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.7)';
        g.x.fillRect(x0, yp, bw, B - yp);
        // velocity head (amber) stacked
        var yv = yOf(hp + hv);
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(251,191,36,0.8)';
        g.x.fillRect(x0, yv, bw, yp - yv);
        label(g.x, labels[k], x0 + bw / 2, B + 14, '#8ea2ad', 9, 'center');
        label(g.x, fmt(hp + hv, 1), x0 + bw / 2, yv - 4, '#c4d2da', 9, 'center');
      }
      // axis
      line(g.x, L, T, L, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      line(g.x, L, B, R, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      label(g.x, 'head (m)', L, T - 2, '#66788a', 9, 'left');
      // legend
      g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.7)'; g.x.fillRect(R - 110, T, 9, 9);
      label(g.x, 'pressure', R - 98, T + 8, '#8ea2ad', 9, 'left');
      g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(251,191,36,0.8)'; g.x.fillRect(R - 110, T + 14, 9, 9);
      label(g.x, 'velocity', R - 98, T + 22, '#8ea2ad', 9, 'left');
    }

    function drawEgl() {
      var g = ctxOf('be_egl'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var L = 30, R = g.w - 14, B = g.h - 24, T = 14;
      var maxH = st.H * 1.12 + 0.4;
      function X(s) { return L + s * (R - L); }
      function Y(val) { return B - (val / maxH) * (B - T); }
      // EGL = total head (constant for ideal flow) ; HGL = p/rho g + z
      var eglPts = [], hglPts = [];
      for (var s = 0; s <= 1.0001; s += 0.02) {
        var vl = localVel(s);
        var pl = localP(s);
        var zl = (s < 0.5) ? st.z2 * (s / 0.5) : st.z2 * (1 - (s - 0.5) / 0.5);
        var hgl = pl / (st.rho * G) + zl;
        var egl = hgl + vl * vl / (2 * G);
        hglPts.push([X(s), Y(hgl)]);
        eglPts.push([X(s), Y(egl)]);
      }
      function poly(pts, col, lw) {
        g.x.beginPath();
        for (var i = 0; i < pts.length; i++) { if (i === 0) g.x.moveTo(pts[i][0], pts[i][1]); else g.x.lineTo(pts[i][0], pts[i][1]); }
        g.x.strokeStyle = col; g.x.lineWidth = lw; g.x.stroke();
      }
      line(g.x, L, T, L, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      line(g.x, L, B, R, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      poly(eglPts, '#5eead4', 2);
      poly(hglPts, '#38bdf8', 2);
      label(g.x, 'EGL (total head)', L + 6, T + 10, '#5eead4', 9, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'HGL', L + 6, T + 24, '#38bdf8', 9, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'pipe length', R, B + 14, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
    }

    anims.push(function () {
      var sec = document.querySelector('.fz-experiment[data-exp="bern"]');
      if (!sec || !sec.classList.contains('active')) return;
      if (st) drawApparatus();
    });
    recompute();
  })();

  /* ================================================================
     EXPERIMENT 2 — REYNOLDS
     ================================================================ */
  (function () {
    var fluidSel = el('re_fluid');
    fillFluidSelect(fluidSel, false);
    fluidSel.value = 'water';
    var dye = []; // dye particles along the tube

    function props() {
      var key = fluidSel.value;
      var f = FLUIDS[key];
      var rho = f.rho, mu = f.mu;
      if (key === 'water') {
        var T = v('re_T');
        rho = waterRho(T);
        mu = waterMu(T);
      }
      return { rho: rho, mu: mu };
    }

    function solve() {
      var p = props();
      var D = v('re_D') / 1000; // m
      var vel = v('re_v');
      var Re = p.rho * vel * D / p.mu;
      var Q = vel * Math.PI * D * D / 4;
      var vc = 2300 * p.mu / (p.rho * D);
      setTxt('re_DV', fmt(v('re_D'), 1));
      setTxt('re_vV', fmt(vel, 2));
      setTxt('re_TV', fmt(v('re_T'), 0));
      setTxt('re_rho', fmt(p.rho, 0) + ' kg/m3');
      setTxt('re_mu', fmt(p.mu * 1000, 3) + ' mPa.s');
      setTxt('re_Re', fmt(Re, 0));
      setTxt('re_Q', fmt(Q * 1e6, 1) + ' cm3/s');
      setTxt('re_vc', fmt(vc, 3) + ' m/s');
      var rEl = el('re_reg');
      if (Re < 2300) { rEl.textContent = 'Laminar'; rEl.className = 'fz-metric-v green'; }
      else if (Re < 4000) { rEl.textContent = 'Transitional'; rEl.className = 'fz-metric-v amber'; }
      else { rEl.textContent = 'Turbulent'; rEl.className = 'fz-metric-v red'; }
      return { rho: p.rho, mu: p.mu, D: D, vel: vel, Re: Re };
    }
    var st = null;
    function recompute() { st = solve(); drawProfile(); }
    var ids = ['re_D', 're_v', 're_T'];
    for (var i = 0; i < ids.length; i++) el(ids[i]).addEventListener('input', recompute);
    fluidSel.addEventListener('change', recompute);
    // T slider only meaningful for water
    el('re_T').addEventListener('input', recompute);

    // temperature control visibility hint not needed

    function drawTube() {
      var g = ctxOf('re_cv'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var left = 70, right = g.w - 20, top = g.h * 0.30, bot = g.h * 0.70;
      var cy = (top + bot) / 2;
      // header tank on the left
      g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.12)';
      g.x.fillRect(8, 20, 56, g.h - 60);
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#2b5a6e'; g.x.lineWidth = 1.5;
      g.x.strokeRect(8, 20, 56, g.h - 60);
      label(g.x, 'tank', 36, 16, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'center');
      // dye reservoir
      g.x.fillStyle = '#b91c4d';
      g.x.fillRect(28, 4, 14, 18);
      label(g.x, 'dye', 35, g.h - 8, '#fca5a5', 9, 'center');
      // glass tube
      g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(120,180,210,0.06)';
      g.x.fillRect(left, top, right - left, bot - top);
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#3a4a55'; g.x.lineWidth = 2;
      g.x.strokeRect(left, top, right - left, bot - top);
      // bell-mouth entry
      line(g.x, 64, 30, left, top, '#2b5a6e', 1.5);
      line(g.x, 64, g.h - 40, left, bot, '#2b5a6e', 1.5);

      // dye filament behaviour depends on Re
      var Re = st.Re;
      var turb = clamp((Re - 2300) / 2200, 0, 1); // 0 laminar .. 1 fully turbulent
      // advance dye particles
      var dt = 0.016;
      // seed
      while (dye.length < 160) dye.push({ s: 0, y0: 0, seed: Math.random() * 100 });
      for (var i = 0; i < dye.length; i++) {
        var d = dye[i];
        d.s += (st.vel / (st.vel + 0.001)) * dt * 0.35 + 0.004;
        if (d.s > 1) { d.s -= 1; d.seed = Math.random() * 100; }
      }
      // draw
      g.x.lineWidth = 2;
      for (var j = 0; j < dye.length; j++) {
        var d2 = dye[j];
        var x = left + d2.s * (right - left);
        // baseline at centre, plus turbulent wander growing downstream
        var wander = 0;
        if (turb > 0) {
          var amp = turb * (bot - top) * 0.46 * d2.s;
          wander = Math.sin(d2.s * 18 + d2.seed + phase * 6) * amp * 0.5
                 + Math.sin(d2.s * 41 + d2.seed * 1.7 - phase * 9) * amp * 0.5;
          // random burst
          wander += (Math.sin(d2.seed * 12.9 + d2.s * 90) ) * amp * 0.4 * turb;
        }
        var y = cy + wander;
        y = clamp(y, top + 3, bot - 3);
        var alpha = 0.85 - turb * 0.35 * d2.s;
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(220,38,90,' + clamp(alpha, 0.25, 0.9) + ')';
        var rad = 1.6 + turb * 1.4 * d2.s;
        g.x.beginPath(); g.x.arc(x, y, rad, 0, 6.283); g.x.fill();
      }
      // regime banner
      var reg = Re < 2300 ? 'LAMINAR — straight dye thread' : (Re < 4000 ? 'TRANSITIONAL — dye wavers' : 'TURBULENT — dye mixes');
      var bcol = Re < 2300 ? '#5eead4' : (Re < 4000 ? '#fbbf24' : '#fca5a5');
      label(g.x, reg, left + 8, top - 8, bcol, 12, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'Re = ' + fmt(Re, 0), right - 8, top - 8, bcol, 12, 'right');
      label(g.x, 'glass tube  D = ' + fmt(v('re_D'), 1) + ' mm', left + 8, bot + 18, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'left');
    }

    function drawProfile() {
      var g = ctxOf('re_prof'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var left = 40, right = g.w - 20, top = 18, bot = g.h - 18;
      var cy = (top + bot) / 2, halfH = (bot - top) / 2 - 4;
      line(g.x, left, top, left, bot, '#2b3d49', 1); // wall
      line(g.x, right - 8, top, right - 8, bot, '#2b3d49', 1);
      line(g.x, left, cy, right, cy, '#16212a', 1);
      var Re = st.Re;
      var turb = clamp((Re - 2300) / 2200, 0, 1);
      // laminar parabolic: u = umax(1-(r/R)^2). turbulent power law u=umax(1-r/R)^(1/7)
      var amp = (right - left) * 0.7;
      g.x.beginPath();
      for (var yy = -1; yy <= 1.0001; yy += 0.02) {
        var rr = Math.abs(yy);
        var lam = 1 - rr * rr;
        var tu = Math.pow(clamp(1 - rr, 0, 1), 1 / 7);
        var u = lam * (1 - turb) + tu * turb;
        var px = left + u * amp;
        var py = cy + yy * halfH;
        if (yy === -1) g.x.moveTo(px, py); else g.x.lineTo(px, py);
      }
      g.x.strokeStyle = Re < 2300 ? '#5eead4' : (Re < 4000 ? '#fbbf24' : '#fca5a5');
      g.x.lineWidth = 2; g.x.stroke();
      // arrows
      for (var ya = -0.8; ya <= 0.8; ya += 0.4) {
        var rr2 = Math.abs(ya);
        var lam2 = 1 - rr2 * rr2;
        var tu2 = Math.pow(clamp(1 - rr2, 0, 1), 1 / 7);
        var u2 = lam2 * (1 - turb) + tu2 * turb;
        var ax = left + u2 * amp, ay = cy + ya * halfH;
        line(g.x, left, ay, ax, ay, 'rgba(125,211,252,0.5)', 1);
        line(g.x, ax, ay, ax - 5, ay - 3, '#7dd3fc', 1);
        line(g.x, ax, ay, ax - 5, ay + 3, '#7dd3fc', 1);
      }
      label(g.x, Re < 2300 ? 'parabolic (laminar)' : (Re < 4000 ? 'transitional' : 'fuller (turbulent)'), right - 8, top + 12, '#c4d2da', 10, 'right');
      label(g.x, 'wall', left - 4, cy, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
    }

    anims.push(function () {
      var sec = document.querySelector('.fz-experiment[data-exp="reyn"]');
      if (!sec || !sec.classList.contains('active')) return;
      if (st) drawTube();
    });
    recompute();
  })();

  /* ================================================================
     EXPERIMENT 3 — PIPE FRICTION / DARCY-WEISBACH / MOODY
     ================================================================ */
  (function () {
    var fluidSel = el('fr_fluid');
    fillFluidSelect(fluidSel, false);
    fluidSel.value = 'water';

    function frictionFactor(Re, eD) {
      if (Re < 1e-6) return 0;
      if (Re < 2300) return 64 / Re;
      // Swamee-Jain explicit (approx Colebrook), valid 4000<Re<1e8, 1e-6<eD<1e-2
      var a = eD / 3.7 + 5.74 / Math.pow(Re, 0.9);
      var f = 0.25 / Math.pow(Math.log(a) / Math.LN10, 2);
      // transitional smoothing 2300..4000
      if (Re < 4000) {
        var fl = 64 / 2300;
        var ft = 0.25 / Math.pow(Math.log(eD / 3.7 + 5.74 / Math.pow(4000, 0.9)) / Math.LN10, 2);
        var t = (Re - 2300) / 1700;
        return fl * (1 - t) + ft * t;
      }
      return f;
    }

    function compute(Q) {
      var f0 = FLUIDS[fluidSel.value];
      var rho = f0.rho, mu = f0.mu;
      var D = v('fr_D') / 1000;
      var L = v('fr_L');
      var e = v('fr_e') / 1000;
      var A = Math.PI * D * D / 4;
      var vel = Q / A;
      var Re = rho * vel * D / mu;
      var eD = e / D;
      var f = frictionFactor(Re, eD);
      var hf = f * (L / D) * vel * vel / (2 * G);
      var dp = rho * G * hf;
      return { rho: rho, mu: mu, D: D, L: L, e: e, eD: eD, A: A, vel: vel, Re: Re, f: f, hf: hf, dp: dp };
    }

    var st = null;
    function recompute() {
      var Q = v('fr_Q') / 1000;
      st = compute(Q);
      setTxt('fr_DV', fmt(v('fr_D'), 0));
      setTxt('fr_LV', fmt(v('fr_L'), 0));
      setTxt('fr_eV', fmt(v('fr_e'), 2));
      setTxt('fr_QV', fmt(v('fr_Q'), 2));
      setTxt('fr_v', fmt(st.vel, 2) + ' m/s');
      setTxt('fr_Re', fmt(st.Re, 0));
      setTxt('fr_eD', fmt(st.eD, 4));
      setTxt('fr_f', fmt(st.f, 4));
      setTxt('fr_hf', fmt(st.hf, 3) + ' m');
      setTxt('fr_dp', fmt(st.dp / 1000, 1) + ' kPa');
      drawMoody();
      drawCurve();
    }
    var ids = ['fr_D', 'fr_L', 'fr_e', 'fr_Q'];
    for (var i = 0; i < ids.length; i++) el(ids[i]).addEventListener('input', recompute);
    fluidSel.addEventListener('change', recompute);

    function drawMoody() {
      var g = ctxOf('fr_moody'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var L = 50, R = g.w - 16, T = 16, B = g.h - 30;
      // x: log Re 2.6..8 ; y: log f 0.008..0.1
      var reLo = 2.6, reHi = 8; // log10
      var fLo = Math.log(0.008) / Math.LN10, fHi = Math.log(0.1) / Math.LN10;
      function X(logRe) { return L + (logRe - reLo) / (reHi - reLo) * (R - L); }
      function Y(logF) { return B - (logF - fLo) / (fHi - fLo) * (B - T); }
      // grid
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#131e26'; g.x.lineWidth = 1;
      for (var lr = 3; lr <= 8; lr++) {
        var gx = X(lr);
        line(g.x, gx, T, gx, B, '#131e26', 1);
        label(g.x, '1e' + lr, gx, B + 14, '#66788a', 9, 'center');
      }
      var fticks = [0.008, 0.01, 0.02, 0.03, 0.05, 0.08, 0.1];
      for (var ft = 0; ft < fticks.length; ft++) {
        var gy = Y(Math.log(fticks[ft]) / Math.LN10);
        line(g.x, L, gy, R, gy, '#131e26', 1);
        label(g.x, fticks[ft].toString(), L - 4, gy + 3, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
      }
      // laminar line f=64/Re for Re 600..2300
      g.x.beginPath();
      var started = false;
      for (var re = 600; re <= 2300; re *= 1.04) {
        var fl = 64 / re;
        var px = X(Math.log(re) / Math.LN10), py = Y(Math.log(fl) / Math.LN10);
        if (!started) { g.x.moveTo(px, py); started = true; } else g.x.lineTo(px, py);
      }
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#5eead4'; g.x.lineWidth = 2; g.x.stroke();
      label(g.x, 'laminar 64/Re', X(3.0), Y(Math.log(64 / 1000) / Math.LN10) - 6, '#5eead4', 9, 'left');
      // turbulent curves for several e/D
      var eDset = [0, 0.0005, 0.002, 0.005, 0.02, 0.05];
      for (var s = 0; s < eDset.length; s++) {
        g.x.beginPath(); var st2 = false;
        for (var re2 = 4000; re2 <= 1e8; re2 *= 1.08) {
          var ff = frictionFactor(re2, eDset[s]);
          var px2 = X(Math.log(re2) / Math.LN10), py2 = Y(Math.log(ff) / Math.LN10);
          if (px2 > R) break;
          if (!st2) { g.x.moveTo(px2, py2); st2 = true; } else g.x.lineTo(px2, py2);
        }
        g.x.strokeStyle = s === 0 ? '#38bdf8' : 'rgba(146,166,179,0.55)';
        g.x.lineWidth = s === 0 ? 2 : 1; g.x.stroke();
        if (s > 0) label(g.x, 'e/D ' + eDset[s], R - 4, Y(Math.log(frictionFactor(8e7, eDset[s])) / Math.LN10) + 3, '#66788a', 8, 'right');
      }
      label(g.x, 'smooth', R - 60, Y(Math.log(frictionFactor(8e7, 0) / 1) / Math.LN10) + 12, '#38bdf8', 8, 'right');
      // operating point
      if (st.Re > 300) {
        var ox = X(clamp(Math.log(st.Re) / Math.LN10, reLo, reHi));
        var oy = Y(clamp(Math.log(st.f) / Math.LN10, fLo, fHi));
        g.x.strokeStyle = '#fbbf24'; g.x.lineWidth = 2;
        line(g.x, ox - 7, oy - 7, ox + 7, oy + 7, '#fbbf24', 2);
        line(g.x, ox - 7, oy + 7, ox + 7, oy - 7, '#fbbf24', 2);
        label(g.x, 'f=' + fmt(st.f, 4), ox + 10, oy - 8, '#fbbf24', 10, 'left');
      }
      label(g.x, 'Reynolds number', (L + R) / 2, B + 26, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'center');
      label(g.x, 'friction factor f', L, T - 4, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'left');
    }

    function drawCurve() {
      var g = ctxOf('fr_curve'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var L = 50, R = g.w - 16, T = 14, B = g.h - 26;
      var Qmax = 40 / 1000;
      // find hf range
      var hfMax = compute(Qmax).hf;
      hfMax = Math.max(hfMax, st.hf) * 1.05 + 1e-6;
      function X(Q) { return L + Q / Qmax * (R - L); }
      function Y(hf) { return B - clamp(hf / hfMax, 0, 1) * (B - T); }
      line(g.x, L, T, L, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      line(g.x, L, B, R, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      g.x.beginPath();
      var first = true;
      for (var q = 0.0005; q <= Qmax; q += Qmax / 160) {
        var c = compute(q);
        var px = X(q), py = Y(c.hf);
        if (first) { g.x.moveTo(px, py); first = false; } else g.x.lineTo(px, py);
      }
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#38bdf8'; g.x.lineWidth = 2; g.x.stroke();
      // current point
      var cx = X(st.A * st.vel), cy = Y(st.hf);
      g.x.fillStyle = '#fbbf24';
      g.x.beginPath(); g.x.arc(cx, cy, 4, 0, 6.283); g.x.fill();
      label(g.x, 'hf = ' + fmt(st.hf, 3) + ' m', cx + 8, cy - 6, '#fbbf24', 10, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'Q (L/s)', R, B + 16, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
      label(g.x, 'head loss (m)', L, T - 2, '#66788a', 9, 'left');
      label(g.x, '0', L, B + 14, '#66788a', 9, 'center');
      label(g.x, '40', R - 10, B + 14, '#66788a', 9, 'center');
    }

    recompute();
  })();

  /* ================================================================
     EXPERIMENT 4 — VENTURI / ORIFICE METER
     ================================================================ */
  (function () {
    var typeBtns = el('ve_type').querySelectorAll('button');
    var driveBtns = el('ve_drive').querySelectorAll('button');
    var meter = 'venturi';
    var drive = 'dp';
    var RHO_W = 998;

    for (var i = 0; i < typeBtns.length; i++) {
      (function (b) {
        b.addEventListener('click', function () {
          for (var j = 0; j < typeBtns.length; j++) typeBtns[j].classList.remove('on');
          b.classList.add('on'); meter = b.getAttribute('data-t'); recompute();
        });
      })(typeBtns[i]);
    }
    for (var k = 0; k < driveBtns.length; k++) {
      (function (b) {
        b.addEventListener('click', function () {
          for (var j = 0; j < driveBtns.length; j++) driveBtns[j].classList.remove('on');
          b.classList.add('on'); drive = b.getAttribute('data-d');
          el('ve_dpwrap').style.display = (drive === 'dp') ? '' : 'none';
          el('ve_qwrap').style.display = (drive === 'q') ? '' : 'none';
          recompute();
        });
      })(driveBtns[k]);
    }

    function cdOf() {
      // venturi ~0.97-0.98, orifice ~0.61-0.64 (mild beta dependence)
      var beta = v('ve_D2') / v('ve_D1');
      if (meter === 'venturi') return 0.975 + 0.004 * (1 - beta);
      return 0.61 + 0.03 * beta;
    }

    var st = null;
    function solve() {
      var D1 = v('ve_D1') / 1000, D2 = v('ve_D2') / 1000;
      if (D2 > D1) { D2 = D1 * 0.95; el('ve_D2').value = (D2 * 1000).toFixed(0); }
      var A1 = Math.PI * D1 * D1 / 4, A2 = Math.PI * D2 * D2 / 4;
      var beta = D2 / D1;
      var sg = v('ve_sg');
      var Cd = cdOf();
      var dp, h, Q, v2, Qi;
      if (drive === 'dp') {
        h = v('ve_h') / 1000; // m deflection
        dp = (sg - 1) * RHO_W * G * h;
        Qi = A2 * Math.sqrt(2 * dp / (RHO_W * (1 - Math.pow(beta, 4))));
        Q = Cd * Qi;
      } else {
        Q = v('ve_q') / 1000;
        Qi = Q / Cd;
        dp = 0.5 * RHO_W * (Qi / A2) * (Qi / A2) * (1 - Math.pow(beta, 4));
        h = dp / ((sg - 1) * RHO_W * G);
      }
      v2 = Q / A2;
      return { D1: D1, D2: D2, A1: A1, A2: A2, beta: beta, Cd: Cd, dp: dp, h: h, Q: Q, Qi: Qi, v2: v2, sg: sg };
    }
    function recompute() {
      st = solve();
      setTxt('ve_D1V', fmt(v('ve_D1'), 0));
      setTxt('ve_D2V', fmt(v('ve_D2'), 0));
      setTxt('ve_sgV', fmt(v('ve_sg'), 1));
      setTxt('ve_hV', fmt(v('ve_h'), 0));
      setTxt('ve_qV', fmt(v('ve_q'), 1));
      setTxt('ve_beta', fmt(st.beta, 3));
      setTxt('ve_cd', fmt(st.Cd, 3));
      setTxt('ve_dp', fmt(st.dp / 1000, 2) + ' kPa');
      setTxt('ve_qi', fmt(st.Qi * 1000, 2) + ' L/s');
      setTxt('ve_qa', fmt(st.Q * 1000, 2) + ' L/s');
      setTxt('ve_v2', fmt(st.v2, 2) + ' m/s');
      setTxt('ve_h_def', fmt(st.h * 1000, 0));
      drawCal();
    }
    var ids = ['ve_D1', 've_D2', 've_sg', 've_h', 've_q'];
    for (var m = 0; m < ids.length; m++) el(ids[m]).addEventListener('input', recompute);

    var vePart = [];
    function drawApp() {
      var g = ctxOf('ve_cv'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var left = 30, right = g.w - 30, span = right - left;
      var midY = g.h * 0.34;
      var r1 = g.h * 0.13, r2 = r1 * st.beta;
      function rAt(s) {
        if (meter === 'venturi') {
          if (s < 0.35) return r1;
          if (s < 0.45) return r1 + (r2 - r1) * (s - 0.35) / 0.10;
          if (s < 0.55) return r2;
          if (s < 0.78) return r2 + (r1 - r2) * (s - 0.55) / 0.23;
          return r1;
        } else {
          // orifice plate: sudden constriction at s=0.5 (vena contracta downstream)
          return r1;
        }
      }
      // pipe body
      g.x.beginPath();
      for (var s = 0; s <= 1.0001; s += 0.01) { var px = left + s * span, py = midY - rAt(s); if (s === 0) g.x.moveTo(px, py); else g.x.lineTo(px, py); }
      for (var s2 = 1; s2 >= -0.0001; s2 -= 0.01) { var px2 = left + s2 * span, py2 = midY + rAt(s2); g.x.lineTo(px2, py2); }
      g.x.closePath();
      g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.07)'; g.x.fill();
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#2b5a6e'; g.x.lineWidth = 2; g.x.stroke();
      // orifice plate
      if (meter === 'orifice') {
        var ox = left + 0.5 * span;
        g.x.fillStyle = '#3a4a55';
        g.x.fillRect(ox - 4, midY - r1, 8, r1 - r2);
        g.x.fillRect(ox - 4, midY + r2, 8, r1 - r2);
      }
      // particles
      while (vePart.length < 70) vePart.push({ s: Math.random(), lane: Math.random() * 2 - 1 });
      var maxV = st.v2;
      for (var i = 0; i < vePart.length; i++) {
        var p = vePart[i];
        var rr = rAt(p.s);
        var localV;
        if (meter === 'venturi') localV = st.Q / (Math.PI * (rr / r1) * (rr / r1) * st.A1) ;
        else localV = (Math.abs(p.s - 0.5) < 0.06) ? st.v2 : st.Q / st.A1;
        p.s += clamp(localV, 0.1, 20) * 0.0016 + 0.002;
        if (p.s > 1) { p.s -= 1; p.lane = Math.random() * 2 - 1; }
        var rad = (meter === 'orifice' && p.s > 0.5 && p.s < 0.62) ? r2 : rAt(p.s);
        var px3 = left + p.s * span, py3 = midY + p.lane * rad * 0.8;
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(125,211,252,0.85)';
        g.x.beginPath(); g.x.arc(px3, py3, 1.9, 0, 6.283); g.x.fill();
      }
      // pressure tap positions
      var x1 = left + 0.2 * span, x2 = left + 0.5 * span;
      // U-tube manometer below
      var baseY = g.h - 18, tubeTop = midY + r1 + 16;
      var mw = 26;
      var mLx = x1, mRx = x2;
      // glass legs
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#3a4a55'; g.x.lineWidth = 1.5;
      g.x.strokeRect(mLx - mw / 2, tubeTop, mw, baseY - tubeTop);
      g.x.strokeRect(mRx - mw / 2, tubeTop, mw, baseY - tubeTop);
      line(g.x, mLx - mw / 2, baseY, mRx + mw / 2, baseY, '#3a4a55', 1.5);
      // connecting lines from taps
      line(g.x, x1, midY - rAt(0.2), x1, tubeTop, '#2b5a6e', 1);
      line(g.x, x2, midY - rAt(0.5), x2, tubeTop, '#2b5a6e', 1);
      // mercury columns: high-pressure side pushed down, low side up
      var maxDefl = baseY - tubeTop - 14;
      var defl = clamp(st.h, 0, maxDefl / 600) ; // scale: h(m) shown but cap
      var dpx = clamp((st.h) / 0.6 * maxDefl, 4, maxDefl); // visual
      var midLevel = (tubeTop + baseY) / 2;
      var leftTop = midLevel + dpx / 2;   // p1 high -> mercury low (further down) on left limb
      var rightTop = midLevel - dpx / 2;  // mercury higher on right
      g.x.fillStyle = '#b0b4bd'; // mercury
      g.x.fillRect(mLx - mw / 2 + 2, leftTop, mw - 4, baseY - leftTop);
      g.x.fillRect(mRx - mw / 2 + 2, rightTop, mw - 4, baseY - rightTop);
      // bottom connector mercury
      g.x.fillRect(mLx - mw / 2 + 2, baseY - 6, mRx - mLx + mw - 4, 6);
      // deflection marker
      line(g.x, mLx - mw / 2 - 6, leftTop, mRx + mw / 2 + 6, leftTop, 'rgba(251,191,36,0.4)', 1);
      line(g.x, mLx - mw / 2 - 6, rightTop, mRx + mw / 2 + 6, rightTop, 'rgba(251,191,36,0.4)', 1);
      label(g.x, 'h = ' + fmt(st.h * 1000, 0) + ' mm', (mLx + mRx) / 2, rightTop - 6, '#fbbf24', 11, 'center');
      label(g.x, 'p1 tap', x1, tubeTop - 4, '#8ea2ad', 9, 'center');
      label(g.x, 'p2 tap', x2, tubeTop - 4, '#8ea2ad', 9, 'center');
      label(g.x, meter === 'venturi' ? 'Venturi meter' : 'Orifice-plate meter', left + 6, midY - r1 - 8, '#5eead4', 12, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'Cd = ' + fmt(st.Cd, 3) + '  Q = ' + fmt(st.Q * 1000, 2) + ' L/s', right - 6, midY - r1 - 8, '#38bdf8', 11, 'right');
    }

    function drawCal() {
      var g = ctxOf('ve_cal'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var L = 44, R = g.w - 14, T = 14, B = g.h - 24;
      // Q vs sqrt(h) straight line
      var hMax = 0.6;
      var sqrtMax = Math.sqrt(hMax);
      // compute Q for max
      var beta = st.beta;
      function Qof(h) {
        var dp = (st.sg - 1) * 998 * G * h;
        var Qi = st.A2 * Math.sqrt(2 * dp / (998 * (1 - Math.pow(beta, 4))));
        return st.Cd * Qi;
      }
      var Qmax = Qof(hMax);
      function X(sq) { return L + sq / sqrtMax * (R - L); }
      function Y(Q) { return B - clamp(Q / (Qmax * 1.02), 0, 1) * (B - T); }
      line(g.x, L, T, L, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      line(g.x, L, B, R, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      g.x.beginPath();
      for (var hh = 0; hh <= hMax; hh += hMax / 80) {
        var px = X(Math.sqrt(hh)), py = Y(Qof(hh));
        if (hh === 0) g.x.moveTo(px, py); else g.x.lineTo(px, py);
      }
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#38bdf8'; g.x.lineWidth = 2; g.x.stroke();
      var cx = X(Math.sqrt(clamp(st.h, 0, hMax))), cy = Y(clamp(st.Q, 0, Qmax));
      g.x.fillStyle = '#fbbf24'; g.x.beginPath(); g.x.arc(cx, cy, 4, 0, 6.283); g.x.fill();
      label(g.x, 'Q proportional to sqrt(h)', L + 8, T + 12, '#5eead4', 10, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'sqrt(deflection)', R, B + 16, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
      label(g.x, 'Q', L - 6, T + 4, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
    }

    anims.push(function () {
      var sec = document.querySelector('.fz-experiment[data-exp="vent"]');
      if (!sec || !sec.classList.contains('active')) return;
      if (st) drawApp();
    });
    recompute();
  })();

  /* ================================================================
     EXPERIMENT 5 — TORRICELLI / TANK DRAINING
     ================================================================ */
  (function () {
    var running = false;
    var h = 2, t = 0, jet = [];
    var At, d, a, Cd, H0;

    function readParams() {
      At = v('to_At');
      d = v('to_d') / 1000;
      a = Math.PI * d * d / 4;
      Cd = v('to_cd');
      H0 = v('to_H');
    }
    function reset() {
      readParams();
      h = H0; t = 0; running = false; jet = [];
      setTxt('to_run', 'Open valve & drain');
      updateReadouts();
      drawCurveTrace();
    }
    function timeToEmpty() {
      return (2 * At / (Cd * a * Math.sqrt(2 * G))) * Math.sqrt(H0);
    }
    function updateReadouts() {
      readParams();
      var vel = Math.sqrt(2 * G * Math.max(h, 0));
      var Q = Cd * a * vel;
      var yOrifice = 0.0; // orifice at base; range measured from a height; use orifice height ~ 0 -> compute range if at mid
      // jet range from orifice located at base: ideal x grows then... use orifice at small height yo
      var yo = 0.15; // orifice slightly above ground for projectile range
      var range = 2 * Math.sqrt(Math.max(h, 0) * yo);
      setTxt('to_AtV', fmt(At, 2));
      setTxt('to_HV', fmt(H0, 2));
      setTxt('to_dV', fmt(v('to_d'), 0));
      setTxt('to_cdV', fmt(Cd, 2));
      setTxt('to_h', fmt(h, 3) + ' m');
      setTxt('to_v', fmt(vel, 2) + ' m/s');
      setTxt('to_Q', fmt(Q * 1000, 2) + ' L/s');
      setTxt('to_x', fmt(range, 2) + ' m');
      setTxt('to_t', fmt(t, 1) + ' s');
      setTxt('to_v0', fmt(Math.sqrt(2 * G * H0), 2) + ' m/s');
      setTxt('to_te', fmt(timeToEmpty(), 1) + ' s');
    }
    var ids = ['to_At', 'to_H', 'to_d', 'to_cd'];
    for (var i = 0; i < ids.length; i++) el(ids[i]).addEventListener('input', function () { if (!running) reset(); });
    el('to_run').addEventListener('click', function () {
      readParams();
      if (h <= 0.001) { h = H0; t = 0; }
      running = !running;
      el('to_run').textContent = running ? 'Pause' : (h <= 0.001 ? 'Refill tank' : 'Resume');
    });
    el('to_reset').addEventListener('click', reset);

    function step(dt) {
      if (!running) return;
      var vel = Math.sqrt(2 * G * Math.max(h, 0));
      var Q = Cd * a * vel;
      var dh = -Q / At * dt;
      h += dh;
      t += dt;
      if (h <= 0) { h = 0; running = false; el('to_run').textContent = 'Refill tank'; }
      updateReadouts();
    }

    function draw() {
      var g = ctxOf('to_cv'); if (!g) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var tankLeft = 60, tankW = 180, tankTop = 30, ground = g.h - 36;
      var tankBot = ground;
      var tankH = tankBot - tankTop;
      // tank walls
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#3a4a55'; g.x.lineWidth = 2;
      g.x.strokeRect(tankLeft, tankTop, tankW, tankH);
      // water level
      var fillFrac = clamp(h / Math.max(H0, 0.001), 0, 1);
      var waterTop = tankBot - fillFrac * tankH;
      g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.25)';
      g.x.fillRect(tankLeft + 2, waterTop, tankW - 4, tankBot - waterTop);
      // surface line
      line(g.x, tankLeft + 2, waterTop, tankLeft + tankW - 2, waterTop, '#38bdf8', 1.5);
      label(g.x, 'h = ' + fmt(h, 2) + ' m', tankLeft + tankW / 2, waterTop - 6, '#7dd3fc', 11, 'center');
      // orifice on right wall near base
      var orY = tankBot - 0.15 / Math.max(H0, 0.001) * tankH; // orifice at 0.15 m above base scaled... clamp
      orY = tankBot - 14;
      var orX = tankLeft + tankW;
      var orR = clamp(d * 200, 3, 10);
      g.x.fillStyle = '#070a0d';
      g.x.fillRect(orX - 3, orY - orR, 6, orR * 2);
      // ground
      line(g.x, 20, ground, g.w - 20, ground, '#2b3d49', 2);

      // jet (projectile) only if water above orifice
      var vel = Math.sqrt(2 * G * Math.max(h, 0));
      if (h > 0.001 && running) {
        // spawn jet particles
        if (jet.length < 120) jet.push({ x: 0, y: 0, vx: vel, vy: 0, life: 0, sp: Math.random() });
      }
      var px2m = tankW / Math.max(H0, 0.5); // px per metre roughly (tank height maps H0)
      var scale = tankH / Math.max(H0, 0.5);
      for (var i = jet.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = jet[i];
        p.life += 0.016;
        // physical projectile from orifice
        var xm = p.vx * p.life;
        var ym = 0.5 * G * p.life * p.life;
        var sx = orX + xm * scale * 0.5;
        var sy = orY + ym * scale * 0.5;
        if (sy > ground || sx > g.w - 10) { jet.splice(i, 1); continue; }
        var alpha = clamp(1 - p.life / 1.5, 0.2, 0.9);
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,' + alpha + ')';
        g.x.beginPath(); g.x.arc(sx, sy, 2.2, 0, 6.283); g.x.fill();
      }
      // velocity vector at orifice
      if (h > 0.001) {
        line(g.x, orX, orY, orX + clamp(vel * 6, 8, 80), orY, '#fbbf24', 2);
        label(g.x, 'v = ' + fmt(vel, 2) + ' m/s', orX + 10, orY - 8, '#fbbf24', 10, 'left');
      }
      label(g.x, 'A_t = ' + fmt(At, 2) + ' m2', tankLeft + 6, tankTop + 14, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'orifice d = ' + fmt(v('to_d'), 0) + ' mm', orX - 100, orY + 22, '#8ea2ad', 9, 'left');
      label(g.x, 't = ' + fmt(t, 1) + ' s', g.w - 24, tankTop + 14, '#c4d2da', 11, 'right');
    }

    function drawCurveTrace() {
      var g = ctxOf('to_curve'); if (!g) return;
      clearCv(g);
      readParams();
      var L = 44, R = g.w - 14, T = 14, B = g.h - 24;
      var te = timeToEmpty();
      function X(tt) { return L + clamp(tt / te, 0, 1) * (R - L); }
      function Y(hh) { return B - clamp(hh / H0, 0, 1) * (B - T); }
      line(g.x, L, T, L, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      line(g.x, L, B, R, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      // theoretical h(t) = (sqrt(H0) - (Cd a sqrt(2g))/(2At) t)^2
      g.x.beginPath();
      var first = true;
      for (var tt = 0; tt <= te; tt += te / 120) {
        var root = Math.sqrt(H0) - (Cd * a * Math.sqrt(2 * G)) / (2 * At) * tt;
        var hh = root > 0 ? root * root : 0;
        var px = X(tt), py = Y(hh);
        if (first) { g.x.moveTo(px, py); first = false; } else g.x.lineTo(px, py);
      }
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#38bdf8'; g.x.lineWidth = 2; g.x.stroke();
      // current marker
      var cx = X(t), cy = Y(h);
      g.x.fillStyle = '#fbbf24'; g.x.beginPath(); g.x.arc(cx, cy, 4, 0, 6.283); g.x.fill();
      label(g.x, 'h(t) — parabolic decay', L + 8, T + 12, '#5eead4', 10, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'time (s)', R, B + 16, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
      label(g.x, 'head h (m)', L, T - 2, '#66788a', 9, 'left');
      label(g.x, 't_empty = ' + fmt(te, 1) + ' s', R - 4, T + 12, '#c4d2da', 9, 'right');
    }

    anims.push(function () {
      var sec = document.querySelector('.fz-experiment[data-exp="torr"]');
      if (!sec || !sec.classList.contains('active')) return;
      step(0.016);
      draw();
      if (running) drawCurveTrace();
    });
    reset();
  })();

  /* ================================================================
     EXPERIMENT 6 — HYDROSTATIC PRESSURE / MANOMETER
     ================================================================ */
  (function () {
    var liqSel = el('ma_liq');
    var LIQS = [
      { n: 'Water', rho: 998 },
      { n: 'Seawater', rho: 1025 },
      { n: 'Oil (SAE10)', rho: 870 },
      { n: 'Glycerin', rho: 1260 },
      { n: 'Mercury', rho: 13600 }
    ];
    for (var i = 0; i < LIQS.length; i++) {
      var o = document.createElement('option'); o.value = i; o.textContent = LIQS[i].n; liqSel.appendChild(o);
    }
    var modeBtns = el('ma_mode').querySelectorAll('button');
    var mode = 'depth';
    for (var k = 0; k < modeBtns.length; k++) {
      (function (b) {
        b.addEventListener('click', function () {
          for (var j = 0; j < modeBtns.length; j++) modeBtns[j].classList.remove('on');
          b.classList.add('on'); mode = b.getAttribute('data-m');
          el('ma_depthp').style.display = (mode === 'depth') ? '' : 'none';
          el('ma_utubep').style.display = (mode === 'utube') ? '' : 'none';
          recompute();
        });
      })(modeBtns[k]);
    }

    var st = null;
    function solve() {
      if (mode === 'depth') {
        var liq = LIQS[parseInt(liqSel.value, 10) || 0];
        var hh = v('ma_h');
        var p0 = v('ma_p0') * 1000;
        var pg = liq.rho * G * hh;
        var pabs = p0 + pg;
        var head = pg / (liq.rho * G);
        var weq = pg / (998 * G);
        return { mode: 'depth', liq: liq, h: hh, p0: p0, pg: pg, pabs: pabs, head: head, weq: weq, defl: 0 };
      } else {
        var pg2 = v('ma_pg') * 1000; // gauge applied
        var sg = v('ma_sg'); var sgc = v('ma_sgc');
        var rhoM = sg * 998, rhoC = sgc * 998;
        var a = v('ma_a');
        // p = (rho_m - rho_c) g h_def + rho_c g a  -> solve h_def
        var hdef = (pg2 - rhoC * G * a) / Math.max((rhoM - rhoC) * G, 1e-6);
        var head = pg2 / (998 * G);
        var weq = head;
        return { mode: 'utube', pg: pg2, rhoM: rhoM, rhoC: rhoC, a: a, defl: hdef, head: head, weq: weq, pabs: pg2 + 101325 };
      }
    }
    function recompute() {
      st = solve();
      if (mode === 'depth') {
        var liq = LIQS[parseInt(liqSel.value, 10) || 0];
        setTxt('ma_liqV', liq.n);
        setTxt('ma_hV', fmt(v('ma_h'), 1));
        setTxt('ma_p0V', fmt(v('ma_p0'), 0));
      } else {
        setTxt('ma_pgV', fmt(v('ma_pg'), 0));
        setTxt('ma_sgV', fmt(v('ma_sg'), 1));
        setTxt('ma_sgcV', fmt(v('ma_sgc'), 3));
        setTxt('ma_aV', fmt(v('ma_a'), 2));
      }
      setTxt('ma_pgauge', fmt(st.pg / 1000, 2) + ' kPa');
      setTxt('ma_pabs', fmt(st.pabs / 1000, 2) + ' kPa');
      setTxt('ma_head', fmt(st.head, 3) + ' m');
      setTxt('ma_defl', st.mode === 'utube' ? fmt(st.defl * 1000, 1) + ' mm' : 'n/a');
      setTxt('ma_weq', fmt(st.weq, 3) + ' m');
      drawApp();
      drawCurve();
    }
    liqSel.addEventListener('change', recompute);
    var ids = ['ma_h', 'ma_p0', 'ma_pg', 'ma_sg', 'ma_sgc', 'ma_a'];
    for (var m = 0; m < ids.length; m++) el(ids[m]).addEventListener('input', recompute);

    function drawApp() {
      var g = ctxOf('ma_cv'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      if (st.mode === 'depth') {
        var liq = st.liq;
        var tankL = 120, tankR = g.w - 120, top = 40, bot = g.h - 30;
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.16)';
        g.x.fillRect(tankL, top, tankR - tankL, bot - top);
        g.x.strokeStyle = '#3a4a55'; g.x.lineWidth = 2;
        g.x.strokeRect(tankL, top, tankR - tankL, bot - top);
        label(g.x, liq.n + '  rho = ' + fmt(liq.rho, 0) + ' kg/m3', tankL + 6, top - 8, '#8ea2ad', 11, 'left');
        // depth scale 0..10 m
        var Hmax = 10;
        function depthY(d) { return top + d / Hmax * (bot - top); }
        for (var dd = 0; dd <= Hmax; dd += 1) {
          var dy = depthY(dd);
          line(g.x, tankL - 6, dy, tankL, dy, '#2b3d49', 1);
          label(g.x, dd + 'm', tankL - 10, dy + 3, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
        }
        // probe
        var py = depthY(v('ma_h'));
        line(g.x, tankL, py, tankR, py, 'rgba(251,191,36,0.4)', 1);
        g.x.fillStyle = '#fbbf24';
        g.x.beginPath(); g.x.arc((tankL + tankR) / 2, py, 6, 0, 6.283); g.x.fill();
        label(g.x, 'p = ' + fmt(st.pg / 1000, 1) + ' kPa (gauge)', (tankL + tankR) / 2 + 12, py - 8, '#fbbf24', 11, 'left');
        label(g.x, 'h = ' + fmt(v('ma_h'), 1) + ' m', (tankL + tankR) / 2 + 12, py + 16, '#c4d2da', 10, 'left');
        // pressure arrows on wall growing with depth
        for (var aD = 0.5; aD < Hmax; aD += 1) {
          var ay = depthY(aD);
          if (ay > bot) break;
          var len = aD / Hmax * 40 + 4;
          line(g.x, tankR, ay, tankR + len, ay, 'rgba(56,189,248,0.6)', 1.5);
        }
        label(g.x, 'pressure with depth', tankR + 8, top + 4, '#38bdf8', 9, 'left');
      } else {
        // U-tube manometer
        var cx = g.w / 2;
        var legGap = 120, legW = 30, topY = 50, botY = g.h - 40;
        var lLx = cx - legGap / 2, rLx = cx + legGap / 2;
        // left limb connects to vessel (applied pressure), right limb open
        g.x.strokeStyle = '#3a4a55'; g.x.lineWidth = 2;
        g.x.strokeRect(lLx - legW / 2, topY, legW, botY - topY);
        g.x.strokeRect(rLx - legW / 2, topY, legW, botY - topY);
        line(g.x, lLx - legW / 2, botY, rLx + legW / 2, botY, '#3a4a55', 2);
        // pressure vessel on left
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.10)';
        g.x.fillRect(20, topY - 10, lLx - legW / 2 - 26, 60);
        g.x.strokeRect(20, topY - 10, lLx - legW / 2 - 26, 60);
        label(g.x, 'applied p', 24, topY - 16, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'left');
        label(g.x, fmt(st.pg / 1000, 1) + ' kPa', 24, topY + 18, '#fbbf24', 12, 'left');
        line(g.x, 20 + (lLx - legW / 2 - 26), topY + 20, lLx - legW / 2, topY + 20, '#2b5a6e', 1.5);
        // mercury fill: defl displaces. mid baseline
        var maxRange = botY - topY - 30;
        var deflPx = clamp(st.defl, -0.5, 0.5) / 0.5 * (maxRange / 2);
        var midL = (topY + botY) / 2;
        // applied pressure pushes left limb mercury down, right up
        var leftTop = midL + deflPx / 2;
        var rightTop = midL - deflPx / 2;
        leftTop = clamp(leftTop, topY + 10, botY - 4);
        rightTop = clamp(rightTop, topY + 10, botY - 4);
        // connected (light) fluid in left limb above mercury
        g.x.fillStyle = 'rgba(56,189,248,0.30)';
        g.x.fillRect(lLx - legW / 2 + 2, topY + 22, legW - 4, leftTop - (topY + 22));
        // mercury
        g.x.fillStyle = '#b0b4bd';
        g.x.fillRect(lLx - legW / 2 + 2, leftTop, legW - 4, botY - leftTop);
        g.x.fillRect(rLx - legW / 2 + 2, rightTop, legW - 4, botY - rightTop);
        g.x.fillRect(lLx - legW / 2 + 2, botY - 6, rLx - lLx + legW - 4, 6);
        // deflection markers
        line(g.x, lLx - legW / 2 - 8, leftTop, rLx + legW / 2 + 8, leftTop, 'rgba(251,191,36,0.35)', 1);
        line(g.x, lLx - legW / 2 - 8, rightTop, rLx + legW / 2 + 8, rightTop, 'rgba(251,191,36,0.35)', 1);
        var deflShown = Math.abs(rightTop - leftTop);
        label(g.x, 'deflection h = ' + fmt(st.defl * 1000, 1) + ' mm', cx, Math.min(leftTop, rightTop) - 8, '#fbbf24', 12, 'center');
        label(g.x, 'open', rLx, topY - 8, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'center');
        label(g.x, 'mercury  SG ' + fmt(v('ma_sg'), 1), cx, botY + 20, '#8ea2ad', 10, 'center');
      }
    }

    function drawCurve() {
      var g = ctxOf('ma_curve'); if (!g || !st) return;
      clearCv(g);
      var L = 50, R = g.w - 14, T = 14, B = g.h - 24;
      var rho = (st.mode === 'depth') ? st.liq.rho : 998;
      var Hmax = 10;
      var pMax = rho * G * Hmax;
      function X(d) { return L + d / Hmax * (R - L); }
      function Y(p) { return B - clamp(p / pMax, 0, 1) * (B - T); }
      line(g.x, L, T, L, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      line(g.x, L, B, R, B, '#2b3d49', 1);
      // linear p = rho g h
      g.x.beginPath();
      g.x.moveTo(X(0), Y(0)); g.x.lineTo(X(Hmax), Y(pMax));
      g.x.strokeStyle = '#38bdf8'; g.x.lineWidth = 2; g.x.stroke();
      if (st.mode === 'depth') {
        var cx = X(v('ma_h')), cy = Y(st.pg);
        g.x.fillStyle = '#fbbf24'; g.x.beginPath(); g.x.arc(cx, cy, 4, 0, 6.283); g.x.fill();
        line(g.x, cx, B, cx, cy, 'rgba(251,191,36,0.3)', 1);
        line(g.x, L, cy, cx, cy, 'rgba(251,191,36,0.3)', 1);
      }
      label(g.x, 'p = rho g h', L + 8, T + 12, '#5eead4', 10, 'left');
      label(g.x, 'depth h (m)', R, B + 16, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
      label(g.x, 'gauge p (Pa)', L, T - 2, '#66788a', 9, 'left');
      label(g.x, fmt(pMax / 1000, 0) + ' kPa', L - 4, T + 6, '#66788a', 9, 'right');
    }

    recompute();
  })();

  requestAnimationFrame(loop);
})();
</script>
</BaseLayout>
